# Third-Party OS & Runtime Licenses

The Script Language Container is distributed as `lc-rs.tar.gz`, built from
`Dockerfile.alpine`. That tarball flattens the entire `alpine:3` root filesystem
**plus** the glibc and GCC runtime libraries copied from the `rust:1.92-bookworm`
(Debian 12) builder stage. This file reproduces the licenses and provides the
source offer for those OS/runtime components.

It is complementary to `THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md`, which (via `cargo about`) covers
only the Rust crate graph statically linked into the `exaudfclient` binary.

**No copyleft propagation.** Every component below is an unmodified upstream
binary shipped as a separate file. glibc is LGPL-2.1; `libstdc++`/`libgcc` carry
the GCC Runtime Library Exception. Nothing here propagates its license to
`exaudfclient` or to user-authored UDFs.

This file is generated by `dist/generate-os-licenses.sh` (see that script);
license texts are rendered by `cargo about` from its embedded SPDX data and are
therefore not committed to the repository.

## Bundled Alpine packages (apk)

| Package(s) | SPDX license |
|------------|--------------|
| alpine-baselayout, alpine-baselayout-data, apk-tools, busybox, busybox-binsh, libapk, scanelf, ssl_client | GPL-2.0-only |
| alpine-keys, alpine-release, musl | MIT |
| musl-utils | MIT AND BSD-2-Clause AND GPL-2.0-or-later |
| ca-certificates, ca-certificates-bundle | MPL-2.0 AND MIT |
| libcrypto3, libssl3 (OpenSSL 3) | Apache-2.0 |
| zlib | Zlib |
| tzdata | Public-Domain |

`tzdata` is public domain and carries no reproduction obligation. The OpenSSL
project's `NOTICE` is satisfied by the Apache-2.0 text reproduced below.

## Bundled glibc / GCC runtime libraries (from Debian 12 `rust:1.92-bookworm`)

| Library file(s) | SPDX license |
|-----------------|--------------|
| `/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6`, `libm.so.6`, `/lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2`, `/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libnss_files.so.2`, `libnss_dns.so.2` | LGPL-2.1-or-later |
| `/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libstdc++.so.6`, `libgcc_s.so.1` | GPL-3.0-or-later WITH GCC-Runtime-Library-Exception |

## Written offer of corresponding source

For the GPL-2.0, LGPL-2.1, and GPL-3.0 components above, the corresponding
source is the unmodified upstream source, available for **three (3) years** from
the date of distribution of this container:

- **Alpine apk packages** — source for the exact package versions is published in
  the Alpine `aports` tree: <https://gitlab.alpinelinux.org/alpine/aports>. The
  installed package versions are recorded in `/lib/apk/db/installed` inside this
  container.
- **glibc and the gcc-12 runtime (libstdc++/libgcc)** — Debian 12 (bookworm)
  source packages `glibc` and `gcc-12`, archived at
  <https://snapshot.debian.org> and mirrored at <https://sources.debian.org>.

A copy of the corresponding source can also be requested through the project
repository at <https://github.com/exasol-labs/language-container-rs> (open an
issue); requests are honored for the three-year period above.

